line_1: The cook-maid raves for want of butter,
line_2: Pigs squeak, fowls scream, and green geese flutter.

line_1: To honest Bounce is Bread and Butter.
line_2: And that to towze such Things as flutter,

line_1: And a kingdom — bread and butter.
line_2: And maps lay all in flutter;
Yet something he was heard to mutter,

line_1: Forsooth! about one's bread and butter.
line_2: But this, you'll say's to make a clutter,
